news.title: UK's Persimmon shares drop amid concerns over rising costs for 2025
news.para: The FTSE 100-listed builder's stock fell by as much as 8% to a more than four-month low of 1,352 pence, underperforming the wider sector, which was down 3% by 1414 GMT.

news.title: Changes to mortgage structure will not resolve housing affordability: Bank of Canada
news.para: "Improved housing affordability requires a better balance between supply and demand, and achieving this balance will take time," Carolyn Rogers said in Toronto in an address on the country's mortgage market.

news.title: Blackstone to acquire Retail Opportunity Investments Corp in $4 billion deal
news.para: Owners of strip malls, pharmacy chains and retail stores have managed to pass on increased costs from high inflation to consumers over the past year, benefiting landlords like ROIC.

news.title: Proposal to revise collector guideline rates on hold at 340 locations in Bhopal
news.para: The committee, which met in the office of registrar general to decide on the proposed revision of rates, gave its nod to hike guideline rates at about 3,500 other locations across the state.

news.title: Visakhapatnam civic body to use drones to verify illegal constructions and layouts
news.para: The concept of drone utilisation emerged from discussions at the recent Drone Summit in Amaravati, focusing on identifying unauthorised building floors and deviations.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body stops issuing A or B khata certificates for sites in illegal layouts
news.para: It's a step towards enforcing stricter regulations and ensuring new developments provide essential infrastructure, a senior BBMP official said.

news.title: Bhopal civic body launches slum rehabilitation project with private sector partnership
news.para: The estimated target population of the survey is around 5 lakh. Prominent slums of the Bhopal located in over 650 acres will come under the purview of the project.

news.title: Property guideline rates increases for 469 locations and 111 new colonies in Indore
news.para: "Indore district evaluation committee had sent a proposal to revise the guideline at 469 existing locations, along with preparing the property rate for 111 newly-developed colonies which the Bhopal-based central evaluation committee approved on Wednesday," senior district registrar Amresh Naidu said.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP mandates registration of C&D sites over 500 sq meter on pollution portal
news.para: The decision, aimed at improving air quality, is part of the state's adherence to the Graded Response Action Plan (GRAP), a framework designed to tackle pollution in NCR's most affected areas.

news.title: West Bengal REAT orders refunds with interest for delayed flat delivery
news.para: Partha Pratim and Aditi Biswas, who booked a 1,250 sqft apartment in New Town for Rs 1.2 crore and paid the entire amount to developer Shristi Infrastructure Development, moved the West Bengal Real Estate Regulatory Authority after the company failed to hand over the flat according to the agreed timeline.

news.title: Ashiana Housing to develop senior living projects in Karnataka and Jaipur
news.para: Ashiana Housing has entered into an agreement to lease to develop a group housing project on a land admeasuring around 20 acres located in the social infrastructure zone of Mahindra World City, Jaipur.

news.title: Telangana RERA directs Bhrigu Infra to refund Rs 20 lakh for not registering plot
news.para: The complainant stated that an agent, representing Bhrigu Infra, enticed them to invest in a 240 square yard villa plot at a rate of 16,000 per square yard with an upfront payment of 20 lakh.

news.title: Telangana RERA penalises Greenspace Housing & Engineers for not registering project
news.para: The case was taken up by TGRERA following a complaint against Greenspace Housing for not registering the project as required under Sections 3 and 4 of the RERA Act.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP begins issuing OCs for S+4 buildings
news.para: On Feb 23, 2023, a govt order restricted construction of four-storey buildings without proper approvals, leading to several of them in licensed colonies going unfinished without OCs.

news.title: Two lakh beneficiaries to soon get 100 sq yard plots: Haryana CM
news.para: Directions have been issued to complete the necessary procedures for this initiative under which five lakh people applied for plots. The beneficiaries will be allotted the plots in a phased manner, Saini said.

news.title: JK Lakshmi Cement posts net loss of Rs 19.24 crore in Q2 FY25
news.para: JK Lakshmi Cement's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,242.67 crore in Q2 FY25, a dip of 21.77 per cent from Rs 1,588.51 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Kansai Nerolac Paints' net profit dips 31.75% in Q2 FY25
news.para: Kansai Nerolac Paints' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,978.07 crore in Q2 FY25 as against Rs 1,978.56 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Aadhar Housing Finance's net profit up 15.31% in Q2 FY25
news.para: Aadhar Housing Finance's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 764.28 crore in Q2 FY25, a growth of 21.57 per cent from Rs 628.67 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Sweden's Skanska posts operating profit of $119.4 million in Q3 2024
news.para: Skanska said its operating profit rose to 1.3 billion Swedish crowns ($119.4 million) from 549 million a year earlier, but missed the 1.67 billion crowns expected by analysts polled by LSEG.
